The body of a man was found submerged in a water canal along the Viljoenskroon Road about 10km from Potchefstroom in North West on Sunday morning, paramedics said. Shortly before 11am paramedics from ER24 arrived on the scene where they found police divers already working on the scene, ER24 spokesman Werner Vermaak said. It is understood that the man was last seen yesterday [Saturday] at 4pm at his house next to the canal. Police divers recovered the man s body. There was nothing that paramedics could do for him and he was declared dead on the scene, he said. African News Agency (ANA)